The McEliece cryptographic system is only enabled for the Linux Qt 5.x project files.

To enable the system for other systems, please follow the following suggestions. Good luck!

1. Verify that libtoon is installed.

2. Create a special libntl target.

libntl.target = libntl.so
libntl.commands = cd ../../libNTL/unix.d/src && ./configure && $(MAKE)
libntl.depends =

Be careful on FreeBSD systems.

libntl.commands = cd ../../libNTL/unix.d/src && ./configure CXX=clang++ && gmake

3. Modify DEFINES.

DEFINES	+= SPOTON_MCELIECE_ENABLED

4. Modify INCLUDEPATH and LIBS.

INCLUDEPATH	+= ../../libNTL/unix.d/include
LIBS		+= -L../../libNTL/unix.d/src/.libs -lntl

Be careful on OS X systems. Use Homebrew!

LIBS		+= -lgmp -lntl

5. Modify QMAKE_CLEAN.

QMAKE_CLEAN += ../../libNTL/unix.d/src/*.o

6. Modify QMAKE_EXTRA_TARGETS and PRE_TARGETDEPS.

QMAKE_EXTRA_TARGETS = libntl libntru libspoton purge
PRE_TARGETDEPS = libntl.so libntru.so libspoton.so
